        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(2 comments)\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> (2 comments)\n> \n> (1)\n> Will there be any writable temp folder, or everything is blocked?\n> I'm asking because at least on a single case, VID is creating a local file on runtime:\n> https://github.com/onap/vid/blob/master/vid-app-common/src/main/java/org/onap/vid/asdc/rest/SdcRestClient.java#L166\n\nWe can create a \"emptyDir\" volume for tmp file creation such as CSAR retrieval\n\n> \n> (2)\n> Where does the pre-configuration take place? Can I see it somewhere, or is it not ready yet?\n\nI didn't worked yet on pre configuration for now (it should be on HELM chart).\n\nAs \"ON_KUBERNETES\" is set to false per default, it shouldn't change for now the default behavior.\nI can make a patch request on OOM for pre configuration if you want.",
